# Performance Guidelines

## Rendering Optimization
- Use proper component lifecycle hooks
- Implement proper lazy loading
- Use proper memoization
- Implement proper virtual scrolling
- Use proper code splitting

## State Management
- Use proper state initialization
- Implement proper state updates
- Use proper computed properties
- Implement proper watchers
- Use proper state persistence

## Asset Optimization
- Optimize images and assets
- Use proper caching strategies
- Implement proper lazy loading
- Use proper compression
- Implement proper CDN usage

## Code Optimization
- Use proper tree shaking
- Implement proper code splitting
- Use proper bundling
- Implement proper minification
- Use proper source maps

## When to Apply
- When optimizing existing code
- When implementing new features
- When reviewing performance
- When fixing performance issues
- When deploying to production 